ciscoSslvpnMIB.name: ciscoSslvpnMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoSslvpnMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-vpn@cisco.com
ciscoSslvpnMIB.description: This MIB module defines management objects for configuration and monitoring of the Cisco secure gateway that implements SSLVPN. Glossary: AnyConnect - Cisco AnyConnect a unified agent that delivers multiple security services to help enable and protect the enterprise. SSL - Secure Sockets Layer URL - Uniform Resource Locator VPN - Virtual Private Network

csslvpnMaxSessionAllowed.name: csslvpnMaxSessionAllowed
csslvpnMaxSessionAllowed.description: This object indicates the maximum number of active SSLVPN sessions that are supported by the device.

csslvpnActiveSessions.name: csslvpnActiveSessions
csslvpnActiveSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of active SSLVPN sessions.

csslvpnPeakSessions.name: csslvpnPeakSessions
csslvpnPeakSessions.description: This object indicates the total number of sessions during peak time.

csslvpnInControlPackets.name: csslvpnInControlPackets
csslvpnInControlPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of control packets received by the Secure Gateway.

csslvpnInDataPackets.name: csslvpnInDataPackets
csslvpnInDataPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of data packets received by the Secure Gateway.

csslvpnOutControlPackets.name: csslvpnOutControlPackets
csslvpnOutControlPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of control packets sent by the Secure Gateway.

csslvpnOutDataPackets.name: csslvpnOutDataPackets
csslvpnOutDataPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of data packets sent by the Secure Gateway.

csslvpnAuthFailures.name: csslvpnAuthFailures
csslvpnAuthFailures.description: This object indicates the total number of authentication failures.

csslvpnConnectFailures.name: csslvpnConnectFailures
csslvpnConnectFailures.description: This object indicates the total number of connect failures.

csslvpnReconnectFailures.name: csslvpnReconnectFailures
csslvpnReconnectFailures.description: This object indicates the total number of reconnect failures.

csslvpnDpdTimeouts.name: csslvpnDpdTimeouts
csslvpnDpdTimeouts.description: This object indicates the total number of Dead Peer Detection timeouts.

csslvpnAuthRequests.name: csslvpnAuthRequests
csslvpnAuthRequests.description: This object indicates the total number of authentication requests.

csslvpnAuthResponses.name: csslvpnAuthResponses
csslvpnAuthResponses.description: This object indicates the total number of authentication responses.

csslvpnInDpdRequests.name: csslvpnInDpdRequests
csslvpnInDpdRequests.description: This object indicates the total number of Dead Peer Detection requests received by Secure Gateway.

csslvpnOutDpdRequests.name: csslvpnOutDpdRequests
csslvpnOutDpdRequests.description: This object indicates the total number of Dead Peer Detection requests sent by Secure Gateway.

csslvpnInDpdResponses.name: csslvpnInDpdResponses
csslvpnInDpdResponses.description: This object indicates the total number of Dead Peer Detection responses received by Secure Gateway.

csslvpnOutDpdResponses.name: csslvpnOutDpdResponses
csslvpnOutDpdResponses.description: This object indicates the total number of Dead Peer Detection responses sent by Secure Gateway.

csslvpnSessionTable.name: csslvpnSessionTable
csslvpnSessionTable.description: A list of SSLVPN sessions which has been successfully created by the secure gateway.

csslvpnSessionEntry.name: csslvpnSessionEntry
csslvpnSessionEntry.description: An entry providing the management information of a SSLVPN session. An entry will be created when the SSLVPN session has been successfully provisioned by the secure gateway. An entry will be removed when the SSLVPN session has been removed by the secure gateway.

csslvpnSessionID.name: csslvpnSessionID
csslvpnSessionID.description: This object indicates the index of a SSLVPN session. The value of csslvpnSessionID is assigned uniquely during session creation.

csslvpnSessionUser.name: csslvpnSessionUser
csslvpnSessionUser.description: This object indicates the username with which session is authenticated.

csslvpnSessionProfile.name: csslvpnSessionProfile
csslvpnSessionProfile.description: This object indicates the SSL profile to which session is connected. The SSL profile defines authentication and accounting lists. Profile selection will be based on policy and URL values. Profile may also optionally associate with default authorization policy

csslvpnSessionPolicy.name: csslvpnSessionPolicy
csslvpnSessionPolicy.description: This object indicates the SSL policy to which session is connected. SSL policy defines the cipher suites to be supported and the trust point to be used during SSL negotiation. SSL policy is a container of all the parameters used in the SSL negotiation. The policy selection would be done by matching the session parameters against the parameters configured under the policy

csslvpnSessionClientIpAddrType.name: csslvpnSessionClientIpAddrType
csslvpnSessionClientIpAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of public IP Address of the client that initiated the session.

csslvpnSessionClientIpAddr.name: csslvpnSessionClientIpAddr
csslvpnSessionClientIpAddr.description: This object indicates the public IP Address of the client that initiated the session. The type of this address is determined by the value of csslvpnSessionClientIpAddrType object.

csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddrType.name: csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddrType
csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of IP address assigned to AnyConnect client during tunnel bring up.

csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddr.name: csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddr
csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address assigned to AnyConnect client during tunnel bring up. The type of this address is determined by the value of csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddrType object.

csslvpnSessionTunnelNetmask.name: csslvpnSessionTunnelNetmask
csslvpnSessionTunnelNetmask.description: This object indicates the netmask assigned to the client during the session bring up. This object is always interpreted with the value of csslvpnSessionTunnelIpAddrType object.

csslvpnSessionNumConnections.name: csslvpnSessionNumConnections
csslvpnSessionNumConnections.description: This object indicates the total number of connections associated with a particular session.

csslvpnSessionRxPackets.name: csslvpnSessionRxPackets
csslvpnSessionRxPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of packets received during the session.

csslvpnSessionTxPackets.name: csslvpnSessionTxPackets
csslvpnSessionTxPackets.description: This object indicates the total number of packets transmitted during the session.

csslvpnSessionRxBytes.name: csslvpnSessionRxBytes
csslvpnSessionRxBytes.description: This object indicates the total number of bytes received during the session.

csslvpnSessionTxBytes.name: csslvpnSessionTxBytes
csslvpnSessionTxBytes.description: This object indicates the total number of bytes transmitted during the session.

csslvpnSessionLastUsed.name: csslvpnSessionLastUsed
csslvpnSessionLastUsed.description: This object indicates the time, when the session was last used.

csslvpnSessionCreated.name: csslvpnSessionCreated
csslvpnSessionCreated.description: This object indicates the time, when the session was created.

csslvpnNotificationEnable.name: csslvpnNotificationEnable
csslvpnNotificationEnable.description: This object specifies whether a specified notification is enabled or not. If a bit corresponding to a notification is set to 1, then the specified notification can be generated. sessionLimit -- the csslvpnSessionLimitNotif notification. tunnelUp -- the csslvpnTunnelUpNotif notification. tunnelDown -- the csslvpnTunnelDownNotif notification.

csslvpnSessionLimitNotif.name: csslvpnSessionLimitNotif
csslvpnSessionLimitNotif.description: This notification would be sent when the attempt of creating a new active sessions may exceed the maximum number of sessions supported by the device.

csslvpnTunnelUpNotif.name: csslvpnTunnelUpNotif
csslvpnTunnelUpNotif.description: This notification would be sent when SSLVPN tunnel gets created.

csslvpnTunnelDownNotif.name: csslvpnTunnelDownNotif
csslvpnTunnelDownNotif.description: This notification would be sent when SSLVPN tunnel tears down.

ciscoSslvpnMIBCompliance.name: ciscoSslvpnMIBCompliance
ciscoSslvpnMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement CISCO-SSLVPN-MIB.

csslvpnGlobalSessionGroup.name: csslvpnGlobalSessionGroup
csslvpnGlobalSessionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management information for global SSLVPN session statistics.

csslvpnStatisticsGroup.name: csslvpnStatisticsGroup
csslvpnStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management information for global SSLVPN statistics.

csslvpnSessionGroup.name: csslvpnSessionGroup
csslvpnSessionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management information for SSLVPN sessions.

csslvpnNotificationControlGroup.name: csslvpnNotificationControlGroup
csslvpnNotificationControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing control on the generation of SSLVPN notifications.
